questions.name: pedigree
questions.title: pedigree
questions.text: Rate this team"s core ability to execute the most challenging aspects of this venture, based on the pedigree of the principals

questions.name: critical skills
questions.title: critical skills
questions.text: Has this team filled all the critical skills gap required to successfully execute this venture?

questions.name: experience&accomplishments
questions.title: experience&accomplishments
questions.text: How close does the team"s prior experience and accomplishments match the most difficult aspects of this venture?

questions.name: commitment
questions.title: commitment
questions.text: Has the team demonstrated the commitment necessary to see this venture through to success?

questions.name: problem strength
questions.title: problem strength
questions.text:
Consider this venture’s offering from the vantage of its audience.  
How strong is the problem, need, or desire being addressed?

questions.name: size of need
questions.title: size of need
questions.text: How many individuals, companies have this need?  How large is the addressable market in your estimate?

questions.name: market growth
questions.title: market growth
questions.text: Is this a market that is growing fast or stagnating/regressing?

questions.name: competition
questions.title: competition
questions.text: How intense is the competition, either direct or indirect?

questions.name: coverage
questions.title: coverage
questions.text: Has the offering/product been previewed by pundits, social media, reviewers.  How positive / negative is the reaction?

questions.name: market support
questions.title: market support
questions.text: How much support is this offering having in the market, either from channel partners, or organic marketing, or press?

questions.name: adoption
questions.title: adoption
questions.text: How fast is the addressable market adopting this product/offering?

questions.name: competitor response
questions.title: competitor response
questions.text: What is the response from competitors (direct/indirect)?

questions.name: core capabilities
questions.title: core capabilities
questions.text: Upon review of the solution, product, technology and core science, how transformative is this team’s offering to the market?

questions.name: review credibility
questions.title: review credibility
questions.text: Has the technology been reviewed by experts(you or other peers) to validate it?  How credible are the ac?

questions.name: technology risk
questions.title: technology risk
questions.text: How risky is this technology/approach?

questions.name: comparitive effectiveness
questions.title: comparitive effectiveness
questions.text:
Comparing this offering with existing/upcoming alternatives.  
How much more effective is it?

questions.name: balance sheet
questions.title: balance sheet
questions.text: Based on audited financials (if available), how strong is its balance sheet and ability to continually invest?

questions.name: revenue / profit momentum
questions.title: revenue / profit momentum
questions.text: Based on audited financials (if available), how strong is the revenue and marginal profit momentum of the company?

questions.name: brand / community support
questions.title: brand / community support
questions.text: How strong is the goodwill (brand or community support) of the company? How strong is the human capital goodwill of the company?

questions.name: intellectual property
questions.title: intellectual property
questions.text: How strong is the intellectual property related to the company’s offering and roadmap?  Does it give it a competitive advantage?

questions.name: number of tokens issued
questions.title: number of tokens issued
questions.text:
Review the schedule of token issuance by the company.
Do you anticipate greater than usual tokens to be offered for sale?

questions.name: vesting schedule / time-locks
questions.title: vesting schedule / time-locks
questions.text:
Review the schedule of vesting / time-locks on tokens in the ecosystem.
Do you anticipate greater than usual tokens to be offered for sale?

questions.name: token demand
questions.title: token demand
questions.text: Based on demand by trade/commercial buyers of tokens, do you anticipate greater than usual tokens to be purchased?

questions.name: speculative demand
questions.title: speculative demand
questions.text: Based on demand by speculative/financial buyers of tokens, do you anticipate greater than usual tokens to be purchased?

questions.name: bull brief
questions.title: bull brief
questions.text: Upon review, can you attest that the Bull valuation brief represents a best-effort, truthful, non-plagiarized, non-conflicted effort by the analyst?

questions.name: bear brief
questions.title: bear brief
questions.text: Upon review, can you attest that the Bear valuation brief represents a best-effort, truthful, non-plagiarized, non-conflicted effort by the analyst?

questions.name: jurist recommendation
questions.title: jurist recommendation
questions.text: After reviewing the Bull and Bear valuation briefs what is your recommendation?
